  lines:
  - character: {fileID: 11400000, guid: a710349f066631f4b9b20cac89af132c, type: 2}
    text: Hmm... how exactly do the HazeBringers we met cause memory loss?
  - character: {fileID: 11400000, guid: c6501bc7a2ffd7e4ea61cfad995a3efb, type: 2}
    text: Well, we think that memories are lost when they are CRYSTALLISED by the
      HazeBringers,
  - character: {fileID: 11400000, guid: c6501bc7a2ffd7e4ea61cfad995a3efb, type: 2}
    text: condensing the memories into memory fragments that look like pink crystals.
  - character: {fileID: 11400000, guid: c6501bc7a2ffd7e4ea61cfad995a3efb, type: 2}
    text: 'Then, if the HazeBringers get their hands on these memory fragments, '
  - character: {fileID: 11400000, guid: c6501bc7a2ffd7e4ea61cfad995a3efb, type: 2}
    text: they can delink the memory from its owner and make it CORRUPTED.
  - character: {fileID: 11400000, guid: c6501bc7a2ffd7e4ea61cfad995a3efb, type: 2}
    text: Once a memory has been crystallised, we can only access it when the Hazebringers
      are trying to corrupt it.
  - character: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 56573228173b49c4aafad1c466d11f01, type: 2}
    text: I still wonder after all this time why they are doing these horrible things...
  - character: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 6afe87506cb9d2141b2204529e4f3f19, type: 2}
    text: "Gaining control over all our memories? \t"
  - character: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 6afe87506cb9d2141b2204529e4f3f19, type: 2}
    text: Maybe it's the government trying to brainwash us into subservient sheeple.
